```

In above code we are filtering out numbers less than 3 and keeping rest of them.

If you want to remove multiple values at once then you can create an array of those values and filter using includes() method

```javascript
let arr = [1, 2, 'a', 'b', 4, 5];
const unwantedValues = ['a', 'b'];
arr = arr.filter(item =>!unwantedValues.includes(item));
console.log(arr); // Output: [1, 2, 4, 5]
```

Remember that these methods will not mutate original arrays but instead returns a new one so be aware of that when assigning result back to same variable name as original array.

